Suggestions API - project name
Can suggest project names based on user query.
--

Get suggestions for project name. The response contains two response parts:

* the first one contains documents matching the query using [ngrams](http://www.elasticsearch.org/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/1.3/analysis-ngram-tokenfilter.html#analysis-ngram-tokenfilter) and [edgengram](http://www.elasticsearch.org/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/1.3/analysis-edgengram-tokenfilter.html) token filters (i.e. exact substring match)
* the second contains documents matching the query using [fuzzy like this query](http://www.elasticsearch.org/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/1.3/query-dsl-flt-query.html#query-dsl-flt-query)

The recommendation is that clients should look for good suggestion candidates in the first response (they should be more relevant then the second response).
The second response should be used for "Did you mean?" scenario or as a fallback if the first response is empty.

##### Request parameters

* `query` is mandatory parameter and is used to generate suggestions.
* `size` of returned result array. Default is 5. Note are two arrays returned in the response. Max value is 100.
* `field` you can use this param multiple times to specify which [fields](http://www.elasticsearch.org/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/1.3/search-request-fields.html) from search index will be returned in results. Fields `sys_project` and `sys_project_name` are always returned as a part of response. Using `field` parameter you can define additional fields to return. If you want complete documents use `_source` value for this param. Be careful about performance impact of this param, consult DCP administrators if necessary!

GET /rest/suggestions/project{?query,size,field}
< 200
< Content-Type: application/json
< Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
{
    "responses" : [
        {
            "hits.hits" : [ ]
        },
        {
            "hits.hits" : [ ] 
        }
    ]
}


